1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:13,089
Now here is where it gets spicy,  this is within-session idempotence only — if the producer process restarts, it gets a new PID and sequence numbers reset.

2
00:00:13,039 --> 00:00:17,947
Cross-session deduplication requires transactional IDs.

3
00:00:17,947 --> 00:00:25,789
Here's something wild: Uber once had a major outage because their apache kafka system failed.

4
00:00:25,789 --> 00:00:28,013
Cost them millions.

5
00:00:28,013 --> 00:00:35,539
At 3 AM, a production server crashed because of Mechanism 3: Read-Committed Consumer.

6
00:00:35,539 --> 00:00:38,723
The entire team was scrambling.

7
00:00:38,723 --> 00:00:42,565
I will show you what went wrong in a minute.

